The paper deals with the problem of optimizing the stability of positive semi-Markov jump linear systems, which is a topic in control theory and systems engineering. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses matrix theory and convex optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.Optimization (Optimization and Control). The paper also discusses an example from population biology, which suggests a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
